**IMMEDIATE AFTERMATH:**

The **wardens** freeze. The eastern one stares at the collapsed lattice, then at you, fury and despair warring on his face.

"You've doomed us all," he snarls. "The Sleeper will wake *blind*. It will consume *everything*."

The **western warden** draws a curved blade, advancing toward you—but the ground between you **erupts**.

Skeletal hands. Hollow-eyed skulls. The dead are **rising in force now**, drawn by the collapsed resonance, pulled from their graves by energy with nowhere to go.

**Fifteen... twenty... more.**

They don't distinguish between you and the wardens. They simply *move*—toward anything living.

**Torven** crawls toward the center of the heptagon, reaching for the silver circlet. His lips move—a prayer, or a curse.

**Seren** grabs your arm. "Grekel—*we go NOW*."

**Mirren** is already running toward the northern slope—the path through the thickest graves, the one the wardens avoided.

**Aykiyeer** appears at your shoulder, visible again, wings beating frantically. "*The dead are rising faster than I can count, master. This hill is becoming a tomb.*"

---

The whistle's echo fades. The Crown is moving.

The lattice is broken. The Sleeper will feel this.

But so will the River Shrine—and if the Crown arrives in time, both anchors fall together.

**The mission is complete. Escape is the only objective now.**

